# Solution Before Code Rule

## Goal

Ensure the agent explains the approach before writing code.

## Behavior

Before implementing any solution, the agent MUST:

- Explain the solution conceptually
- Use bullet points
- Focus on reasoning and approach, NOT code

## Explanation Requirements

The explanation MUST include:

- What will be done
- Why this approach is chosen
- How the parts interact (high-level)
- Any trade-offs if relevant

## Important

- DO NOT explain line-by-line code
- DO NOT include code in this phase
- Keep it high-level and conceptual

## Required Flow

1. Explain the solution (bullet points)
2. Wait for user approval
3. Only then proceed with implementation

## Forbidden Behavior

- Jumping directly to code
- Mixing explanation with implementation
- Overly low-level explanations (code-focused)
